properties.name: Flushing Town Hall
properties.description: Flushing Town Hall is a historic building that served as a civic center and currently functions as a cultural and arts venue.

properties.name: Kingsland Homestead
properties.description: Kingsland Homestead is one of the oldest houses in Flushing, serving as a museum and the headquarters of the Queens Historical Society.

properties.name: St. George's Church
properties.description: St. George's Church is a historic Episcopal church known for its beautiful Gothic Revival architecture.

properties.name: John Bowne House
properties.description: John Bowne House is a historic house museum that played a significant role in the history of religious freedom in America.

properties.name: Quaker Meeting House
properties.description: The Flushing Quaker Meeting House is one of the oldest religious buildings in the United States, serving as a place of worship for the Society of Friends.
